# Token economy

Always-on habits for lean context. Edit-size limits and chat lifecycle live in `context-hygiene` — do not duplicate them here.

## Read / search

- Do not re-read files or outputs already in context.
- Large files: read with `offset`/`limit`, not whole-file.
- Search with Grep/Glob tools, not shell; in terminal use `rg`, not `grep -r`/`find`.
- Prefer Grep for a symbol over reading the whole file.

## Shell output

- Bound output: `| head -n`, `--tail`, `-n`, or check size with `wc -l` first.
- Do not `cat` large files — use Read with a range.

## Context & replies

- Independent tool calls in one batch.
- Broad codebase exploration → `Task`/subagent so dumps stay out of the main thread.
- Brief answers; cite `path:lines` instead of pasting large code/logs.
- Do not dump secrets/env files wholesale — touch only the variables you need.

Detail playbook: skill `token-saver` (explicit “frugal” / “token-saver” only).
